flowRoot.flowPara: The response of the coil is measured for N samples after trigger. We do this for each coil in turn.
We trigger and record the coil M times. With each trigger, we sum up all the ADC values. We then take the average value over the M sample series.
We publish a message to the CAN bus.
One message always encodes the values of two coils. Each coil value is a 16-bit int. The message is defined as:
The COIL_REGISTER identifies which coils the two values belong to.
The message is transmitted on the CAN-bus to a CAN-to-USB receiver.
The CAN messages are published via the can-utils on a linux-can device (slcan0)
The canbridge from the metaldetector_ros package unpacks the CAN messages and publishes them on topics.
The topic names are defined in metaldetector_ros/config.
The canbridge will strip the COIL_REGISTER from the message and intepret and publish the remaining bytes as one INT32.
The metalnode from the metaldetector_ros package parses the messages from the canbridge and separates them into single values again.
